76561197998178631,Not Recommended,229580,28826919,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,AtOnYcK,"I truly wish I could leave a RECOMMENDED review, but I just can’t. Do not buy this game for full price, and only carefully consider it with a big discount.Biggest YEPS:- The graphics and general level design are really pretty to look at and wander through.- Beautiful music, very fitting for the surroundings!- Some puzzles were beautifully designed, making solving them very satisfying.Biggest NOPES:- You have to take itslooowlywith this game, because it doesn’t allow you to rush through any of it. Want to grab a map? Let me build it up atom by atom. Want to run around the house? A shame, best I can do is this walking-through-a-meter-of-honey pace. You redid a section? Well that’s lovely, listen to this 5 minute unskippable dialogue again, since you enjoyed it so much the first time.- Quite often tedious puzzles, some of which broken, so a restart of the game was necessary a couple of times in my case.More pro’s:- I liked the way we got to learn more and more about the main characters, giving the player little snippets here and there, ending it all with a nice message.- The Nightmare sections do feel very much like a nightmare and are most unsettling.More cons:- Not having any clue on where to go, what to collect and how to solve certain sections.- Dull voice overs and lots of cheap typo’s in the subtitles, or that the things that were said deviated from the subtitles.- The game doesn’t tell you any of the buttons. FYI: Shift is sprint in the dreamworld, and mouse scroll is switching between collected items, use them with the key F, and using the alarm clock wakes you up.- Weird character collision. (so I can glitch through the washing machine, but I can’t fit through that 4 feet wide gap?)- I wrongfully received the Runner achievement. Perhaps because I explored all of the mazes before I finishing my first one safely.- *Looks at Global Achievements* Only 12.6% finished act one, 4.3% finished act two, 2,5% finished act three and even less people finished the game. That says enough.Again, I really tried to like this game! But just too many things bothered me to make it anenjoyableexperience. Finished the game with a 'moderate' ending. All fine by me, I'm not putting in any more hours to find all the collectable stuff; merely finishing it is tedious enough."
