76561198050803811,Recommended,229580,9115477,"Posted: 14 February, 2014",all,campbellmc14,"Dream is a good adventure game filled with lots of puzzles. Currently, the game suffers from quite a few bugs, but the game is still in its alpha stage for a reason. The game's mood swings from being relaxing to moderately scary. Scary enough that you start to get goosebumps, but not so scary that you want to turn off the game, which is good. I have yet to find anything in the game that can 'kill' you, though there is at least one enemy in the game.Despite being a good game, it does have flaws.The game's biggest flaw, I'd have to say, is that the game never gives you any idea as to what you're supposed to do. This does have some upsides to it for fans of exploration, though players trying to simply get on with 'the main quest' (if one even exists) will find themselves a bit annoyed. Also, it'd be nice for there to be a part of the map that tells you where you are right then and there, so you don't get lost.As for its strengths, it has plenty. Personally, I enjoy listening to the protagonist. He has a good sense of humor, and allows some of the darker parts of the game to be a bit more bearable. Also, the surreal environments are just gorgeous. Also, the game never holds your hand, which is also a very good thing.Over all, I'd say if you like surreal environments, exploration, don't mind just a touch of horror, then this game will be worth your money."
