,Recommended,229580,32204152,Posted: 5 June,all,HLK,"I enjoyed this game. I didn't enjoy it so much at first, and I think that's unfortunate. The Desert level is confusing, large, and suffers from the most non-intuitive issues. But after reading some guides here on Steam I was able to figure out what I needed to do and progress in the game, and subsequent levels are much better. It has many very good puzzles that I personally didn't find too frustrating or confusing, though I have seen many complaints about them. I honestly wasn't expecting the quality of puzzles that I got.In a few ways the game reminded me of Myst (though not anywhere near as frustrating - you might not know what the puzzle is for as you're completing it in Dream, but they are much easier to understand and are self-contained, e.g. you don't need to complete part of a puzzle in one world and part in another). There were also many things about the game that reminded me of The Stanley Parable (some of the mazes with rooms that change as you move through them, and other trippy effects like the ""MC Escher"" level).The graphics are very good in my opinion - after all, it (reportedly, I am unable to test this) has VR support. In some areas they may test your hardware a bit (the snow upon completing the first level comes to mind). The levels are also much bigger than a typical game of this scope, and as someone who loves exploring, that was really entertaining to me. However, there are still some mysteries left in the game even after completing it. I'm really not sure if I missed something, despite getting the ""best"" ending.Overall I thought it was a good value for the price - comparing it to going out for a cheap meal or going to the movies, I definitely got much more value for my money and enjoyment from this game.After completing the game I wrote a walkthrough of the whole thing to help other people out - consider it an ""extended review"" if you want more information on the game."
